Last Updated: 10-Nov-2025

SamTask (“App”), developed by SunSam Apps, provides task management features.
This Privacy Policy explains how your information is collected, used, and protected.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information (Optional)

We may collect:

Name or email (only if you log in or enable cloud backup)

If you use the app offline without login, we do not collect personal information.

1.2 Non-Personal Information

We may collect:

Device type

Operating system version

App performance and crash data

Anonymous usage information

1.3 Children’s Data

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.
If a child uses the app, no personal data is required.

2. How We Use the Information

We use information to:

Save and manage tasks

Sync tasks if cloud backup is enabled

Improve app features and performance

Diagnose crashes and technical issues

Support future ads (non-personalized)

We never sell your data.

3. Data Storage & Security

Data is stored securely on your device or cloud services (e.g., Vercel, Firebase, Supabase).

We use reasonable security measures to protect your data.

4. Sharing of Information

We do not share data with third parties except:

Service providers (hosting, backup, analytics)

To comply with legal requirements

To prevent fraud or abuse

We do not sell or trade personal information.

5. Third-Party Services Used

The app may use:

Firebase Authentication (login)

Firebase/Firestore/Supabase (backup & sync)

Vercel APIs (cloud functions)

Crashlytics (crash reporting)

AdMob / Google Ads (when ads are added later)

These services may collect anonymous device data.

6. Advertising (AdMob)

In future updates, SamTask may show ads using Google AdMob.

✅ Important Rules We Follow

No personalized ads for children

No tracking across apps or websites for kids

Ads shown to children are strictly non-personalized

AdMob may collect:

Device identifiers

Approximate location

App usage analytics

No sensitive data is collected.

If you add ads later:

Users will be shown a Consent Prompt (Google UMP or Funding Choices).

Users may choose to allow or deny ad personalization.

7. User Rights

You can request:

Access to your data

Correction of information

Complete deletion of your account and personal data

Contact details are provided below.

8. Children’s Privacy (COPPA)

We comply with COPPA and Google Play’s Family Policy:

No personal data collected from children

Only non-personalized ads will be shown

Parents can request deletion at any time

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy for feature changes or legal updates.
You will be notified in the app or via updates.

